The 2019 Cloud Conference, hosted by MyBroadband, will be hosted on 6 June 2019 at Gallagher Estate in Midrand, Gauteng. It is the premier cloud event in South Africa and the meeting place for the country’s IT and cloud community. Every year South Africa’s top cloud companies, hosting and data centre players, and cloud communications providers join the conference to exhibit their products and interact with IT decision makers. Liquid Telecom, a premier cloud and ICT provider in Africa, has joined the conference as the lead sponsor. Other prominent companies which will exhibit at the event include Connection Telecom, VMWare, Fortinet, Cipherwave, Westcon, Redstor, and Elingo. Radio 702’s Aki Anastasiou will be emcee at the event, with speakers from all the major cloud players in South Africa set to participate. To get an overview of the MyBroadband Cloud Conference, a short promotional video about the event is below. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>